Language name: AIZI
Language number: 4131
Alternate names: 
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Kru
Comments: Vowel harmony based on tongue root position is 
prevalent in Aizi.  /a/ is neutral and /i,e,o,u/ are 
opposed to the remaining vowels.  Aizi is tonal but the 
number of tones is uncertain.

Sources: 

Herault, G. 1971. L'Aizi: Esquisse phonologique et enquete 
lexicale.  Institut de Linguistique Appliquee, Unversite 
d'Abidjan, Abidjan.